<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/un-panel-final-push-climate-report-194927760.html"><img src="http://l2.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/3CnZtnjgAzj6_1wvTMI6Zg--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3M7Zmk9ZmlsbDtoPTg2O3E9ODU7dz0xMzA-/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/afp.com/c281377de92f303e048bee81baede2c5e6da740c.jpg" width="130" height="86" alt="Smoke rising from stacks of a thermal power station in Sofia on February 14, 2013" align="left" title="Smoke rising from stacks of a thermal power station in Sofia on February 14, 2013" border="0" /></a>Stockholm (AFP) - Scientists and governments pored over the summary Thursday of an eagerly awaited UN report expected to emphasise the escalating threat from climate change.</p><br clear="all"/>
